-- Poland's Netia plans share buy-back worth up to $66 mln
-- By Marcin Goettig
-- Thu Apr 24, 2014 11:59AM EDT
-- None



WARSAW, April 24 (Reuters) - Poland's second-largest telecoms company Netia <NET.WA> plans to buy back shares worth up to 200 million zlotys ($65.8 million), or up to 20 percent of its existing capital, the company said on Thursday in draft resolutions for its shareholder meeting.

Netia said it aims to complete the buyback within three years.